https://parivarthan.shivtechnologies.com/user/Userlogin 1. The login screen should include fields for email and password, along with a login call-to-action (CTA).
2. Validation criteria for login credentials should be in place (As per Ninja portal).
3. Only users validated as members of the Business Team should be allowed to log in, verified through information from the ninja portal.
4. Upon successful login, the home page dashboard should display information about projects mapped to the logged-in Business Team.
5. Each project displayed on the dashboard should show:
- Number of new requests and breakdown (absorbed, approved, rejected).
- PMO of the project must also be mentioned (Data to be fecthed from Ninja)
- If there are more than one PMO then +1,+2 accordingly to be mentioned and when hovered over it the other PMO(+1,+2) mapped to it must be displayed and lead must be shown first.
- Number of CRs requested, including:
* Number of requests absorbed, approved, and rejected.
- Number of NRs requested, including:
* Number of requests absorbed, approved, and rejected.
6. Only projects with CRs or NRs raised should be displayed on the dashboard.
7. The dashboard should feature a header with a notification bell and user profile button, similar to the ninja portal.
Note: Validate the business team member as lead or not and if lead give the edit or else only the view access.		 Using Email and ID on login page Business team can go dahsboard page and see all project.  Project will load according to user login.
